# Mission 4 – Microsoft 365 Administration

## Overview

Mission 4 focused on the day-to-day responsibilities of a Microsoft 365 Administrator by applying structured troubleshooting and administrative reasoning to realistic production scenarios. The mission was designed around responsibilities commonly found in Microsoft 365 Administrator and IT Operations roles, particularly the position of IT Operations & Systems Administrator.

Rather than memorizing portal navigation or product features, the objective was to develop an engineering approach to troubleshooting Microsoft 365 services by identifying business impact, determining scope, eliminating unaffected services, gathering evidence, identifying the root cause, and validating the resolution.

Throughout this mission, every scenario reinforced the distinction between authentication, licensing, provisioning, and authorization while strengthening the ability to communicate a structured investigation during technical interviews.

