## Engineering Methodology

Every scenario throughout this mission followed the same troubleshooting framework.

1. Determine the business impact.
2. Identify whether the issue affects one user or multiple users.
3. Eliminate services that are functioning correctly.
4. Identify whether the issue relates to authentication, licensing, provisioning, or authorization.
5. Verify the affected configuration.
6. Compare with a known working user whenever possible.
7. Gather evidence before making changes.
8. Implement the appropriate resolution.
9. Validate the result.
10. Document the findings for future reference.

This structured methodology reduces unnecessary changes, accelerates root cause identification, and provides consistent communication during incident handling.

