## Mission Outcome

Mission 4 strengthened my understanding of Microsoft 365 administration by teaching me to troubleshoot from an operational perspective rather than focusing on individual settings. The emphasis was placed on logical investigation, service dependencies, and user lifecycle management instead of memorizing administrative interfaces.

More importantly, this mission reinforced the habit of using evidence-based troubleshooting, allowing me to confidently explain my reasoning during technical interviews while following real-world administrative practices.
